  "type": "weapon",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This heavy, reinforced helmet can be used to make melee attacks. The wearer may use the helmet when attempting&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Bull-Rush\">bull rush</a>&nbsp;maneuvers, granting a +2&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Circumstance-Bonus\">circumstance bonus</a>&nbsp;on the check, but after completing the maneuver (whether successful or not), the wearer is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Staggered\">staggered</a>&nbsp;until the end of his next turn.</p>\n<p>In addition, a dwarven boulder helmet grants a +2&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Circumstance-Bonus\">circumstance bonus</a>&nbsp;to the wearer’s AC against&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Critical-Hits\">critical hit</a>&nbsp;confirmation rolls. A dwarven boulder helmet can be enchanted as a weapon (not as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Armor-Bonus\">armor</a>, despite providing some protection).</p>\n<p>A dwarven boulder helmet adds 20% to the wearer’s arcane spell failure chance. It occupies the head slot and is made of metal, not stone, meaning that it can be crafted from unusual materials as a metal weapon.</p>",
      "chat": "",
      "unidentified": ""
    },
